                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I left him 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. and some accounts, which he got in directly—he had no leave to sell things—I asked my brother to pay him while I was in the country, but he got more than sufficient on the first Sa<lb></lb>turday to pay himself, and on the second Saturday he went to my brother—he has received 18<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. over his wages—I gave him 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. a week—he knew that I was coming home—I came home on the Thursday, and went out for some refreshment—when I came back the shop was shut, and he was gone—on Friday morning he came at ten, instead of seven, as he ought—I questioned him, and he gave me a very unsatisfactory account of the money—I did not give him in charge till the Monday.</p>
